title: Grateful Dead Live at Radio City Music Hall on 1980-10-27
lineage: Master AUD (Sony ECM-280/D-5) Cass> PCM> ZA2> CD
description: The Race is On, I've Been All Around This World, Monkey & The Engineer, To Lay Me Down, Heaven Help The Fool, Rosalie McFall, On The Road Again, Bird Song-> Ripple Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Peggy-O, Passenger, Row Jimmy, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal Truckin'-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text: This sounds as good as the Senn 421s I can't really tell the difference, maybe someone with a better ear can.  Excellent recording!

One of A Kind Truckin>Scarlet>Fire! The Band is ON throughout this show- I've never been much of a fan of GD or Jerry Band accoustic but it can serve as one hell of a warm up- and by the time they open the 3rd with Truckin and push it right into Scarlet Begonias without missing a spiraling sounding beat, only to finish by spitting out one of the GREATEST Fire's ever played, it's become a show performed at a time now frozen in history... But it's a time that's always open to those who know how to feel the freaky magic made in it's chaotic space!
